<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-09T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-09T06:00:00-05:00" n="614" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/7117: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-09T19:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">July 9,
                                            1920—7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 9—1:49
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>166. The following telegram has been received from Stevens: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>Harbin, July 6, 10 p.m. Orders are issued for the evacuation
                                        Japanese troops from the Trans-Baikal region. Destination is
                                        unknown. At their request we are sending 2000 box and 200
                                        passenger cars for the movement.</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <p>Repeated Tokyo.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>